Kubernetes Monitoring Setup: Helm + Prometheus + Grafana
1️⃣ Install Prerequisites
1.1 Install Helm (v3+)
# On Ubuntu/Debian
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
helm version

Verify you have Helm v3 or later.

1.2 Ensure kubectl is installed and configured
kubectl version --client
kubectl get nodes

Make sure your kubeconfig points to the cluster.

2️⃣ Add Helm Repositories
helm repo add prometheus-community https://prometheus-community.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo add grafana https://grafana.github.io/helm-charts
helm repo update

Output should show:

"prometheus-community" has been added to your repositories
"grafana" has been added to your repositories
Update Complete. ⎈Happy Helming!⎈
3️⃣ Install kube-prometheus-stack
helm install kube-prometheus-stack prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  -n monitoring --create-namespace

Check installation:

kubectl get pods -n monitoring -l "release=kube-prometheus-stack"
4️⃣ Check Pod Status
kubectl get pods -n monitoring -w

Pods to watch:

Pod	Expected Status
grafana	3/3 Running
kube-state-metrics	1/1 Running
prometheus	2/2 Running
alertmanager	2/2 Running
operator	1/1 Running
node-exporter	1/1 Running

Wait for all pods to be fully ready; some may take 1–2 minutes.

5️⃣ Access Grafana
5.1 Get Admin Password
kubectl get secret -n monitoring kube-prometheus-stack-grafana \
  -o jsonpath="{.data.admin-password}" | base64 -d
5.2 Port-Forward Grafana Service
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/kube-prometheus-stack-grafana 3000:80

Open browser: http://localhost:3000

Username: admin

Password: (from step 5.1)

6️⃣ Verify Metrics in Grafana

Login to Grafana.

Go to Dashboards → Kubernetes → Compute Resources → Node (Pods)

Go to Dashboards → Kubernetes → Compute Resources → Cluster

Wait a few minutes if metrics show No data.

7️⃣ Verify Prometheus Metrics
kubectl exec -n monitoring <prometheus-pod-name> -- curl -s http://localhost:9090/metrics | head

Should display raw Prometheus metrics.

If empty, check kube-state-metrics and node-exporter pods.

8️⃣ Grafana Data Source Check

Grafana → Configuration → Data Sources → Prometheus

URL: http://kube-prometheus-stack-prometheus.monitoring.svc:9090

Click Save & Test → should show Data source is working.

9️⃣ Access Alertmanager
kubectl port-forward -n monitoring svc/kube-prometheus-stack-alertmanager 9093:9093

Open browser: http://localhost:9093

Monitor alerts and silences.

🔟 Troubleshooting

CrashLoopBackOff / Pod Errors:

kubectl logs -n monitoring <pod-name>
kubectl describe pod -n monitoring <pod-name>

No data in Grafana:

Check Prometheus targets: kubectl exec -n monitoring <prometheus-pod-name> -- curl http://localhost:9090/targets

Ensure metrics are being scraped by Prometheus.

Network/Port issues:

Ensure local firewall allows port-forward.

Use correct namespace monitoring.

✅ Summary

Helm installed and updated.

kube-prometheus-stack deployed in namespace monitoring.

Grafana accessible via http://localhost:3000.

Prometheus scraping metrics from node-exporter and kube-state-metrics.

Alertmanager running for alerts.

Dashboards ready for CPU, Memory, Network usage, Pods, Deployments, StatefulSets, and DaemonSets.

